#. lang="pi"><section class="sutta" id="dn34"><article><div class="hgroup"><p
#. class="division">
msgctxt "dn34:1.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 34"
msgstr "Long Discourses 34"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1"
msgid "Dasuttarasutta"
msgstr "Up to Ten"

#. </h1></div><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.1"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts3.272"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:3.1"
msgid "<span class=\"evam\">Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​</span>"
msgstr "<span class=”evam”>So I have heard.</span>"

msgctxt "dn34:3.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā campāyaṃ viharati gaggarāya pokkharaṇiyā tīre mahatā "
"bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Campā on the banks of the Gaggara "
"Lotus Pond together with a large Saṅgha of five hundred mendicants."

msgctxt "dn34:3.3"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn34:3.4"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "dn34:3.5"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "dn34:3.6"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:"
msgstr "Sāriputta said this:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:4.1"
msgid "“Dasuttaraṃ pavakkhāmi,"
msgstr "“I will relate the teachings"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:4.2"
msgid "dhammaṃ nibbānapattiyā;"
msgstr "up to ten for attaining extinguishment."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:4.3"
msgid "Dukkhassantakiriyāya,"
msgstr "for making an end of suffering,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:4.4"
msgid "sabbaganthappamocanaṃ."
msgstr "the release from all ties."

#. </p></blockquote><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:5.1"
msgid "1. Eko dhammo"
msgstr "Groups of One"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.2"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:6.1"
msgid ""
"Eko, āvuso, dhammo bahukāro, eko dhammo bhāvetabbo, eko dhammo pariññeyyo, "
"eko dhammo pahātabbo, eko dhammo hānabhāgiyo, eko dhammo visesabhāgiyo, eko "
"dhammo duppaṭivijjho, eko dhammo uppādetabbo, eko dhammo abhiññeyyo, eko "
"dhammo sacchikātabbo."
msgstr ""
"Reverends, one thing is helpful, one thing should be developed, one thing "
"should be completely understood, one thing should be given up, one thing "
"makes things worse, one thing leads to distinction, one thing is hard to "
"penetrate, one thing should be produced, one thing should be directly known, "
"one thing should be realized."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:7.1"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo bahukāro?"
msgstr "What one thing is helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:7.2"
msgid "Appamādo kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr "Diligence in skillful qualities."

msgctxt "dn34:7.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo bahukāro. <span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:8.1"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo bhāvetabbo?"
msgstr "What one thing should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:8.2"
msgid "Kāyagatāsati sātasahagatā."
msgstr "Mindfulness of the body that is full of pleasure."

msgctxt "dn34:8.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo bhāvetabbo. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:9.1"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo pariññeyyo?"
msgstr "What one thing should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:9.2"
msgid "Phasso sāsavo upādāniyo."
msgstr ""
"Contact, which is accompanied by defilements and is prone to being grasped."

msgctxt "dn34:9.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo pariññeyyo. <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.273"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:10.1"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo pahātabbo?"
msgstr "What one thing should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:10.2"
msgid "Asmimāno."
msgstr "The conceit ‘I am’."

msgctxt "dn34:10.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo pahātabbo. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:11.1"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo hānabhāgiyo?"
msgstr "What one thing makes things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:11.2"
msgid "Ayoniso manasikāro."
msgstr "Irrational focus."

msgctxt "dn34:11.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo hānabhāgiyo. <span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:12.1"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo visesabhāgiyo?"
msgstr "What one thing leads to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:12.2"
msgid "Yoniso manasikāro."
msgstr "Rational focus."

msgctxt "dn34:12.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo visesabhāgiyo. <span class=\"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:13.1"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo duppaṭivijjho?"
msgstr "What one thing is hard to penetrate?"

msgctxt "dn34:13.2"
msgid "Ānantariko cetosamādhi."
msgstr "The heart’s immersion of immediate result."

msgctxt "dn34:13.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo duppaṭivijjho. <span class=\"brnum\">(7)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:14.1"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo uppādetabbo?"
msgstr "What one thing should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:14.2"
msgid "Akuppaṃ ñāṇaṃ."
msgstr "Unshakable knowledge."

msgctxt "dn34:14.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo uppādetabbo. <span class=\"brnum\">(8)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:15.1"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo abhiññeyyo?"
msgstr "What one thing should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:15.2"
msgid "Sabbe sattā āhāraṭṭhitikā."
msgstr "All sentient beings are sustained by food."

msgctxt "dn34:15.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo abhiññeyyo. <span class=\"brnum\">(9)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:16.1"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo sacchikātabbo?"
msgstr "What one thing should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:16.2"
msgid "Akuppā cetovimutti."
msgstr "The unshakable heart’s release."

msgctxt "dn34:16.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo sacchikātabbo. <span class=\"brnum\">(10)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:17.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ime dasa dhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā tathāgatena "
"abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these ten things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:18.1"
msgid "2. Dve dhammā"
msgstr "Groups of Two"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.3"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:19.1"
msgid ""
"Dve dhammā bahukārā, dve dhammā bhāvetabbā, dve dhammā pariññeyyā, dve "
"dhammā pahātabbā, dve dhammā hānabhāgiyā, dve dhammā visesabhāgiyā, dve "
"dhammā duppaṭivijjhā, dve dhammā uppādetabbā, dve dhammā abhiññeyyā, dve "
"dhammā sacchikātabbā."
msgstr ""
"Two things are helpful, two things should be developed, two things should be "
"completely understood, two things should be given up, two things make things "
"worse, two things lead to distinction, two things are hard to penetrate, two "
"things should be produced, two things should be directly known, two things "
"should be realized."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:20.1"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What two things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:20.2"
msgid "Sati ca sampajaññañca."
msgstr "Mindfulness and situational awareness."

msgctxt "dn34:20.3"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā bahukārā. <span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:21.1"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What two things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:21.2"
msgid "Samatho ca vipassanā ca."
msgstr "Serenity and discernment."

msgctxt "dn34:21.3"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā bhāvetabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:22.1"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What two things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:22.2"
msgid "Nāmañca rūpañca."
msgstr "Mental and physical phenomena."

msgctxt "dn34:22.3"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā pariññeyyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.274"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:23.1"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What two things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:23.2"
msgid "Avijjā ca bhavataṇhā ca."
msgstr "Ignorance and craving to be reborn. "

msgctxt "dn34:23.3"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā pahātabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:24.1"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What two things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:24.2"
msgid "Dovacassatā ca pāpamittatā ca."
msgstr "Being hard to correct and having bad friends."

msgctxt "dn34:24.3"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā hānabhāgiyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:25.1"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What two things lead to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:25.2"
msgid "Sovacassatā ca kalyāṇamittatā ca."
msgstr "Being easy to correct and having good friends."

msgctxt "dn34:25.3"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā visesabhāgiyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:26.1"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What two things are hard to penetrate?"

msgctxt "dn34:26.2"
msgid ""
"Yo ca hetu yo ca paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya, yo ca hetu yo ca paccayo "
"sattānaṃ visuddhiyā."
msgstr ""
"What are the causes and conditions for the corruption of sentient beings, "
"and what are the causes and conditions for the purification of sentient "
"beings."

msgctxt "dn34:26.3"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā duppaṭivijjhā. <span class=\"brnum\">(7)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:27.1"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What two things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:27.2"
msgid "Dve ñāṇāni—"
msgstr "Two knowledges:"

msgctxt "dn34:27.3"
msgid "khaye ñāṇaṃ, anuppāde ñāṇaṃ."
msgstr "knowledge of ending, and knowledge of non-arising."

msgctxt "dn34:27.4"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā uppādetabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(8)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:28.1"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What two things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:28.2"
msgid "Dve dhātuyo—"
msgstr "Two elements:"

msgctxt "dn34:28.3"
msgid "saṅkhatā ca dhātu asaṅkhatā ca dhātu."
msgstr "the conditioned element and the unconditioned element."

msgctxt "dn34:28.4"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā abhiññeyyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(9)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:29.1"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What two things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:29.2"
msgid "Vijjā ca vimutti ca."
msgstr "Knowledge and freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:29.3"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā sacchikātabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(10)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:30.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ime vīsati dhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā "
"tathāgatena abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these twenty things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:31.1"
msgid "3. Tayo dhammā"
msgstr "Groups of Three"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.4"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:32.1"
msgid "Tayo dhammā bahukārā, tayo dhammā bhāvetabbā …"
msgstr "Three things are helpful, etc."

msgctxt "dn34:32.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:32.3"
msgid "tayo dhammā sacchikātabbā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:33.1"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What three things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:33.2"
msgid "Sappurisasaṃsevo, saddhammassavanaṃ, dhammānudhammappaṭipatti."
msgstr ""
"Associating with good people, listening to the true teaching, and practicing "
"in line with the teaching."

msgctxt "dn34:33.3"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā bahukārā. <span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:34.1"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What three things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:34.2"
msgid "Tayo samādhī—"
msgstr "Three kinds of immersion."

msgctxt "dn34:34.3"
msgid ""
"savitakko savicāro samādhi, avitakko vicāramatto samādhi, avitakko avicāro "
"samādhi."
msgstr ""
"Immersion with placing the mind and keeping it connected. Immersion without "
"placing the mind, but just keeping it connected. Immersion without placing "
"the mind or keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "dn34:34.4"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā bhāvetabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.275"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:35.1"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What three things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:35.2"
msgid "Tisso vedanā—"
msgstr "Three feelings:"

msgctxt "dn34:35.3"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā."
msgstr "pleasant, painful, and neutral."

msgctxt "dn34:35.4"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā pariññeyyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:36.1"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What three things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:36.2"
msgid "Tisso taṇhā—"
msgstr "Three cravings:"

msgctxt "dn34:36.3"
msgid "kāmataṇhā, bhavataṇhā, vibhavataṇhā."
msgstr ""
"craving for sensual pleasures, craving for continued existence, and craving "
"to terminate existence."

msgctxt "dn34:36.4"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā pahātabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:37.1"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What three things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:37.2"
msgid "Tīṇi akusalamūlāni—"
msgstr "Three unskillful roots:"

msgctxt "dn34:37.3"
msgid "lobho akusalamūlaṃ, doso akusalamūlaṃ, moho akusalamūlaṃ."
msgstr "greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "dn34:37.4"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā hānabhāgiyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:38.1"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What three things lead to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:38.2"
msgid "Tīṇi kusalamūlāni—"
msgstr "Three skillful roots:"

msgctxt "dn34:38.3"
msgid "alobho kusalamūlaṃ, adoso kusalamūlaṃ, amoho kusalamūlaṃ."
msgstr "non-greed, non-hate, and non-delusion."

msgctxt "dn34:38.4"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā visesabhāgiyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:39.1"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What three things are hard to penetrate?"

msgctxt "dn34:39.2"
msgid "Tisso nissaraṇiyā dhātuyo—"
msgstr "Three elements of escape."

msgctxt "dn34:39.3"
msgid ""
"kāmānametaṃ nissaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ nekkhammaṃ, rūpānametaṃ nissaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ "
"arūpaṃ, yaṃ kho pana kiñci bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ, nirodho "
"tassa nissaraṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Renunciation is the escape from sensual pleasures. The formless is the "
"escape from form. Cessation is the escape from whatever is created, "
"conditioned, and dependently originated."

msgctxt "dn34:39.4"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā duppaṭivijjhā. <span class=\"brnum\">(7)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:40.1"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What three things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:40.2"
msgid "Tīṇi ñāṇāni—"
msgstr "Three knowledges:"

msgctxt "dn34:40.3"
msgid "atītaṃse ñāṇaṃ, anāgataṃse ñāṇaṃ, paccuppannaṃse ñāṇaṃ."
msgstr "regarding the past, future, and present."

msgctxt "dn34:40.4"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā uppādetabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(8)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:41.1"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What three things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:41.2"
msgid "Tisso dhātuyo—"
msgstr "Three elements:"

msgctxt "dn34:41.3"
msgid "kāmadhātu, rūpadhātu, arūpadhātu."
msgstr "sensual, form, and formless."

msgctxt "dn34:41.4"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā abhiññeyyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(9)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:42.1"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What three things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:42.2"
msgid "Tisso vijjā—"
msgstr "Three knowledges:"

msgctxt "dn34:42.3"
msgid ""
"pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇaṃ vijjā, sattānaṃ cutūpapāte ñāṇaṃ vijjā, āsavānaṃ "
"khaye ñāṇaṃ vijjā."
msgstr ""
"recollection of past lives, knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient "
"beings, and knowledge of the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "dn34:42.4"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā sacchikātabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(10)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.276"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:43.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ime tiṃsa dhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā tathāgatena "
"abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these thirty things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:44.1"
msgid "4. Cattāro dhammā"
msgstr "Groups of Four"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.5"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:45.1"
msgid "Cattāro dhammā bahukārā, cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā …"
msgstr "Four things are helpful, etc."

msgctxt "dn34:45.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:45.3"
msgid "cattāro dhammā sacchikātabbā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:46.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What four things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:46.2"
msgid "Cattāri cakkāni—"
msgstr "Four situations:"

msgctxt "dn34:46.3"
msgid ""
"patirūpadesavāso, sappurisūpanissayo, attasammāpaṇidhi, pubbe ca katapuññatā."
msgstr ""
"living in a suitable region, relying on good people, right determination, "
"and past merit."

msgctxt "dn34:46.4"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā bahukārā. <span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:47.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What four things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:47.2"
msgid "Cattāro satipaṭṭhānā—"
msgstr "The four kinds of mindfulness meditation."

msgctxt "dn34:47.3"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya "
"loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body, keen, aware, and "
"mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "dn34:47.4"
msgid "Vedanāsu …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "dn34:47.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:47.6"
msgid "citte …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "dn34:47.7"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles, keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world. "

msgctxt "dn34:47.8"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:48.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What four things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:48.2"
msgid "Cattāro āhārā—"
msgstr "Four foods:"

#. VAR: kabaḷīkāro → kavaḷīkāro (s1-3, km) | kabaliṅkāro (pts1)
msgctxt "dn34:48.3"
msgid ""
"kabaḷīkāro āhāro oḷāriko vā sukhumo vā, phasso dutiyo, manosañcetanā tatiyā, "
"viññāṇaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
"solid food, whether coarse or fine; contact is the second, mental intention "
"the third, and consciousness the fourth. "

msgctxt "dn34:48.4"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā pariññeyyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:49.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What four things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:49.2"
msgid "Cattāro oghā—"
msgstr "Four floods:"

msgctxt "dn34:49.3"
msgid "kāmogho, bhavogho, diṭṭhogho, avijjogho."
msgstr "sensuality, desire for rebirth, views, and ignorance."

msgctxt "dn34:49.4"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā pahātabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:50.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What four things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:50.2"
msgid "Cattāro yogā—"
msgstr "Four bonds:"

msgctxt "dn34:50.3"
msgid "kāmayogo, bhavayogo, diṭṭhiyogo, avijjāyogo."
msgstr "sensuality, desire for rebirth, views, and ignorance."

msgctxt "dn34:50.4"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā hānabhāgiyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:51.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What four things lead to distinction?"

#. VAR: visaṃyogā → visaññogā (^dn33#146 [Saṅgītisutta/4. Catukka])
msgctxt "dn34:51.2"
msgid "Cattāro visaṃyogā —"
msgstr "Four kinds of detachment:"

msgctxt "dn34:51.3"
msgid ""
"kāmayogavisaṃyogo, bhavayogavisaṃyogo, diṭṭhiyogavisaṃyogo, "
"avijjāyogavisaṃyogo."
msgstr ""
"detachment from the bonds of sensuality, desire for rebirth, views, and "
"ignorance."

msgctxt "dn34:51.4"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā visesabhāgiyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="46"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.277"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:52.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What four things are hard to penetrate?"

msgctxt "dn34:52.2"
msgid "Cattāro samādhī—"
msgstr "Four kinds of immersion:"

# In my view, this is almost certainly a mistake. Four sannas are more plausibly described in this way at AN 4.179. The sanskrit text at SF 107 has the four noble truths, which makes much more sense. 
msgctxt "dn34:52.3"
msgid ""
"hānabhāgiyo samādhi, ṭhitibhāgiyo samādhi, visesabhāgiyo samādhi, "
"nibbedhabhāgiyo samādhi."
msgstr ""
"immersion liable to decline, stable immersion, immersion that leads to "
"distinction, and immersion that leads to penetration."

msgctxt "dn34:52.4"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā duppaṭivijjhā. <span class=\"brnum\">(7)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="47"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:53.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What four things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:53.2"
msgid "Cattāri ñāṇāni—"
msgstr "Four knowledges:"

msgctxt "dn34:53.3"
msgid "dhamme ñāṇaṃ, anvaye ñāṇaṃ, pariye ñāṇaṃ, sammutiyā ñāṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"knowledge of the present phenomena, knowledge of what follows, knowledge of "
"other’s minds, and conventional knowledge."

msgctxt "dn34:53.4"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā uppādetabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(8)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="48"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:54.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What four things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:54.2"
msgid "Cattāri ariyasaccāni—"
msgstr "The four noble truths:"

#. VAR: dukkhanirodhaṃ → dukkhanirodho (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn34:54.3"
msgid ""
"dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ, dukkhasamudayaṃ ariyasaccaṃ, dukkhanirodhaṃ "
"ariyasaccaṃ, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṃ."
msgstr ""
"suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of suffering, and the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of suffering."

msgctxt "dn34:54.4"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā abhiññeyyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(9)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="49"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:55.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What four things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:55.2"
msgid "Cattāri sāmaññaphalāni—"
msgstr "Four fruits of the ascetic life:"

msgctxt "dn34:55.3"
msgid "sotāpattiphalaṃ, sakadāgāmiphalaṃ, anāgāmiphalaṃ, arahattaphalaṃ."
msgstr "stream-entry, once-return, non-return, perfection."

msgctxt "dn34:55.4"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā sacchikātabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(10)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="50"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:56.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ime cattārīsadhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā "
"tathāgatena abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these forty things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:57.1"
msgid "5. Pañca dhammā"
msgstr "Groups of Five"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="51"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.6"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:58.1"
msgid "Pañca dhammā bahukārā …"
msgstr "Five things are helpful, etc."

msgctxt "dn34:58.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:58.3"
msgid "pañca dhammā sacchikātabbā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="52"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:59.1"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What five things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:59.2"
msgid "Pañca padhāniyaṅgāni—"
msgstr "Five factors that support meditation."

msgctxt "dn34:59.3"
msgid "idhāvuso, bhikkhu saddho hoti, saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:"
msgstr "A mendicant has faith in the Realized One’s awakening: "

msgctxt "dn34:59.4"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfect, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme trainer of people, "
"teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "dn34:59.5"
msgid ""
"Appābādho hoti appātaṅko samavepākiniyā gahaṇiyā samannāgato nātisītāya "
"nāccuṇhāya majjhimāya padhānakkhamāya."
msgstr ""
"They are rarely ill or unwell. Their stomach digests well, being neither too "
"hot nor too cold, but just right, and fit for meditation. "

msgctxt "dn34:59.6"
msgid ""
"Asaṭho hoti amāyāvī yathābhūtamattānaṃ āvīkattā satthari vā viññūsu vā "
"sabrahmacārīsu."
msgstr ""
"They’re not devious or deceitful. They reveal themselves honestly to the "
"Teacher or sensible spiritual companions."

msgctxt "dn34:59.7"
msgid ""
"Āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"They live with energy roused up for giving up unwholesome qualities and "
"gaining wholesome qualities. They’re strong, firmly applied, not slacking "
"off when it comes to developing wholesome qualities."

msgctxt "dn34:59.8"
msgid ""
"Paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya "
"sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"They’re wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is "
"noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering."

msgctxt "dn34:59.9"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā bahukārā. <span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="53"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.278"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:60.1"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What five things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:60.2"
msgid "Pañcaṅgiko sammāsamādhi—"
msgstr "Right immersion with five factors:"

msgctxt "dn34:60.3"
msgid ""
"pītipharaṇatā, sukhapharaṇatā, cetopharaṇatā, ālokapharaṇatā, "
"paccavekkhaṇanimittaṃ."
msgstr ""
"pervaded with rapture, pervaded with pleasure, pervaded with mind, pervaded "
"with light, the basis for reviewing."

msgctxt "dn34:60.4"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="54"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:61.1"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What five things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:61.2"
msgid "Pañcupādānakkhandhā —"
msgstr "Five sets of phenomena connected with grasping:"

msgctxt "dn34:61.3"
msgid ""
"rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, "
"saṅkhārupādānakkhandho viññāṇupādānakkhandho."
msgstr ""
"the grasping aggregates of form, feeling, perception, choices, and "
"consciousness."

msgctxt "dn34:61.4"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā pariññeyyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="55"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:62.1"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What five things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:62.2"
msgid "Pañca nīvaraṇāni—"
msgstr "Five hindrances:"

msgctxt "dn34:62.3"
msgid ""
"kāmacchandanīvaraṇaṃ, byāpādanīvaraṇaṃ, thinamiddhanīvaraṇaṃ, "
"uddhaccakukkuccanīvaraṇaṃ, vicikicchānīvaraṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"sensual desire, ill will, dullness and drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, "
"and doubt."

msgctxt "dn34:62.4"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā pahātabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="56"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:63.1"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What five things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:63.2"
msgid "Pañca cetokhilā—"
msgstr "Five kinds of emotional barrenness."

msgctxt "dn34:63.3"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu satthari kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, a mendicant has doubts about the Teacher. They’re uncertain, "
"undecided, and lacking confidence."

msgctxt "dn34:63.4"
msgid ""
"Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu satthari kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na "
"sampasīdati, tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya."
msgstr ""
"This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, "
"persistence, and endeavor. "

msgctxt "dn34:63.5"
msgid "Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:63.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo cetokhilo."
msgstr "This is the first kind of emotional barrenness."

msgctxt "dn34:63.7"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu dhamme kaṅkhati vicikicchati …"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant has doubts about the teaching … "

msgctxt "dn34:63.8"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:63.9"
msgid "saṅghe kaṅkhati vicikicchati …"
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "dn34:63.10"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:63.11"
msgid "sikkhāya kaṅkhati vicikicchati …"
msgstr "the training … "

msgctxt "dn34:63.12"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:63.13"
msgid ""
"sabrahmacārīsu kupito hoti anattamano āhatacitto khilajāto, yo so, āvuso, "
"bhikkhu sabrahmacārīsu kupito hoti anattamano āhatacitto khilajāto, tassa "
"cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant is angry and upset with their spiritual companions, resentful "
"and closed off."

msgctxt "dn34:63.14"
msgid "Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya."
msgstr ""
"This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, "
"persistence, and endeavor.  "

msgctxt "dn34:63.15"
msgid "Ayaṃ pañcamo cetokhilo."
msgstr "This is the fifth kind of emotional barrenness."

msgctxt "dn34:63.16"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā hānabhāgiyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="57"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:64.1"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What five things lead to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:64.2"
msgid "Pañcindriyāni—"
msgstr "Five faculties:"

msgctxt "dn34:64.3"
msgid ""
"saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ."
msgstr "faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom."

msgctxt "dn34:64.4"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā visesabhāgiyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="58"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:65.1"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What five things are hard to penetrate?"

msgctxt "dn34:65.2"
msgid "Pañca nissaraṇiyā dhātuyo—"
msgstr "Five elements of escape."

msgctxt "dn34:65.3"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhuno kāme manasikaroto kāmesu cittaṃ na pakkhandati na "
"pasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant focusses on sensual pleasures, but their mind isn’t eager, "
"confident, steady, and decided about them. "

msgctxt "dn34:65.4"
msgid ""
"Nekkhammaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto nekkhamme cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati "
"santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"But when they focus on renunciation, their mind is eager, confident, steady, "
"and decided about it. "

msgctxt "dn34:65.5"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ visaṃyuttaṃ "
"kāmehi."
msgstr ""
"Their mind is in a good state, well developed, well risen, well freed, and "
"well detached from sensual pleasures."

msgctxt "dn34:65.6"
msgid "Ye ca kāmapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātā pariḷāhā, mutto so tehi."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of sensual pleasures, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn34:65.7"
msgid "Na so taṃ vedanaṃ vedeti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn34:65.8"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ kāmānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "This is how the escape from sensual pleasures is explained."

msgctxt "dn34:65.9"
msgid "(7.1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="59"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:66.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno byāpādaṃ manasikaroto byāpāde cittaṃ na "
"pakkhandati na pasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take another case where a mendicant focusses on ill will, but their mind isn’"
"t eager …"

msgctxt "dn34:66.2"
msgid ""
"Abyāpādaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto abyāpāde cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati "
"santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr "But when they focus on love, their mind is eager …"

msgctxt "dn34:66.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ visaṃyuttaṃ "
"byāpādena."
msgstr "Their mind is in a good state … well detached from ill will."

msgctxt "dn34:66.4"
msgid "Ye ca byāpādapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātā pariḷāhā, mutto so tehi."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of ill will, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "dn34:66.5"
msgid "Na so taṃ vedanaṃ vedeti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:66.6"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ byāpādassa nissaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "This is how the escape from ill will is explained."

msgctxt "dn34:66.7"
msgid "(7.2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="60"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:67.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno vihesaṃ manasikaroto vihesāya cittaṃ na "
"pakkhandati na pasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take another case where a mendicant focusses on harming, but their mind isn’"
"t eager …"

msgctxt "dn34:67.2"
msgid ""
"Avihesaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto avihesāya cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati "
"santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr "But when they focus on compassion, their mind is eager …"

msgctxt "dn34:67.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ visaṃyuttaṃ "
"vihesāya."
msgstr "Their mind is in a good state … well detached from harming."

msgctxt "dn34:67.4"
msgid "Ye ca vihesāpaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātā pariḷāhā, mutto so tehi."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of harming, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "dn34:67.5"
msgid "Na so taṃ vedanaṃ vedeti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:67.6"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ vihesāya nissaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "This is how the escape from harming is explained."

msgctxt "dn34:67.7"
msgid "(7.3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="61"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:68.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno rūpe manasikaroto rūpesu cittaṃ na "
"pakkhandati na pasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take another case where a mendicant focusses on form, but their mind isn’t "
"eager …"

msgctxt "dn34:68.2"
msgid ""
"Arūpaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto arūpe cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati "
"santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr "But when they focus on the formless, their mind is eager …"

msgctxt "dn34:68.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ visaṃyuttaṃ "
"rūpehi."
msgstr "Their mind is in a good state … well detached from forms."

msgctxt "dn34:68.4"
msgid "Ye ca rūpapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātā pariḷāhā, mutto so tehi."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of form, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "dn34:68.5"
msgid "Na so taṃ vedanaṃ vedeti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:68.6"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ rūpānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "This is how the escape from forms is explained."

msgctxt "dn34:68.7"
msgid "(7.4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="62"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:69.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno sakkāyaṃ manasikaroto sakkāye cittaṃ na "
"pakkhandati na pasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take a case where a mendicant focusses on identity, but their mind isn’t "
"eager, confident, steady, and decided about it. "

msgctxt "dn34:69.2"
msgid ""
"Sakkāyanirodhaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto sakkāyanirodhe cittaṃ pakkhandati "
"pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"But when they focus on the ending of identity, their mind is eager, "
"confident, steady, and decided about it. "

msgctxt "dn34:69.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ visaṃyuttaṃ "
"sakkāyena."
msgstr ""
"Their mind is in a good state, well developed, well risen, well freed, and "
"well detached from identity."

msgctxt "dn34:69.4"
msgid "Ye ca sakkāyapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātā pariḷāhā, mutto so tehi."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of identity, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "dn34:69.5"
msgid "Na so taṃ vedanaṃ vedeti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:69.6"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ sakkāyassa nissaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "This is how the escape from identity is explained."

msgctxt "dn34:69.7"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā duppaṭivijjhā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:69.8"
msgid "(7.5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="63"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.279"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:70.1"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What five things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:70.2"
msgid "Pañca ñāṇiko sammāsamādhi:"
msgstr "Right immersion with five knowledges."

msgctxt "dn34:70.3"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ samādhi paccuppannasukho ceva āyatiñca sukhavipāko’ti paccattaṃyeva "
"ñāṇaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr ""
"The following knowledges arise for you personally: ‘This immersion is "
"blissful now, and results in bliss in the future.’ "

msgctxt "dn34:70.4"
msgid "‘Ayaṃ samādhi ariyo nirāmiso’ti paccattaññeva ñāṇaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr "‘This immersion is noble and spiritual.’ "

msgctxt "dn34:70.5"
msgid "‘Ayaṃ samādhi akāpurisasevito’ti paccattaṃyeva ñāṇaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr "‘This immersion is not cultivated by corrupt people.’ "

msgctxt "dn34:70.6"
msgid ""
"‘Ayaṃ samādhi santo paṇīto paṭippassaddhaladdho ekodibhāvādhigato, na "
"sasaṅkhāraniggayhavāritagato’ti paccattaṃyeva ñāṇaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr ""
"‘This immersion is peaceful and sublime and tranquil and unified, not held "
"in place by forceful suppression.’"

msgctxt "dn34:70.7"
msgid ""
"‘So kho panāhaṃ imaṃ samādhiṃ satova samāpajjāmi sato vuṭṭhahāmī’ti "
"paccattaṃyeva ñāṇaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr "‘I mindfully enter into and emerge from this immersion.’ "

msgctxt "dn34:70.8"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā uppādetabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(8)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="64"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:71.1"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What five things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:71.2"
msgid "Pañca vimuttāyatanāni—"
msgstr "Five opportunities for freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:71.3"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhuno satthā dhammaṃ deseti aññataro vā garuṭṭhāniyo "
"sabrahmacārī."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, the Teacher or a respected spiritual companion teaches Dharma to a "
"mendicant. "

#. VAR: tathā so → bhikkhu (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn34:71.4"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, āvuso, bhikkhuno satthā dhammaṃ deseti, aññataro vā "
"garuṭṭhāniyo sabrahmacārī tathā tathā so tasmiṃ dhamme atthappaṭisaṃvedī ca "
"hoti dhammapaṭisaṃvedī ca."
msgstr ""
"That mendicant feels inspired by the meaning and the teaching in that "
"Dharma, no matter how the Teacher or a respected spiritual companion teaches "
"it."

msgctxt "dn34:71.5"
msgid ""
"Tassa atthappaṭisaṃvedino dhammapaṭisaṃvedino pāmojjaṃ jāyati, pamuditassa "
"pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, "
"sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Feeling inspired, gladness springs up. Being joyful, rapture springs up. "
"When the mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. When the body "
"is tranquil, one feels bliss. And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed."

msgctxt "dn34:71.6"
msgid "Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ vimuttāyatanaṃ."
msgstr "This is the first opportunity for freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:71.7"
msgid "(9.1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="65"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn34:72.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno na heva kho satthā dhammaṃ deseti, aññataro "
"vā garuṭṭhāniyo sabrahmacārī, api ca kho yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ "
"vitthārena paresaṃ deseti yathā yathā, āvuso, bhikkhu yathāsutaṃ "
"yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ vitthārena paresaṃ deseti tathā tathā so tasmiṃ "
"dhamme atthappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti dhammapaṭisaṃvedī ca."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, it may be that neither the Teacher nor a respected spiritual "
"companion teaches Dharma to a mendicant. But the mendicant teaches Dharma in "
"detail to others as they learned and memorized it. That mendicant feels "
"inspired by the meaning and the teaching in that Dharma, no matter how they "
"teach it in detail to others as they learned and memorized it."

msgctxt "dn34:72.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa atthappaṭisaṃvedino dhammapaṭisaṃvedino pāmojjaṃ jāyati, pamuditassa "
"pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, "
"sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Feeling inspired, gladness springs up. Being joyful, rapture springs up. "
"When the mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. When the body "
"is tranquil, one feels bliss. And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed."

msgctxt "dn34:72.3"
msgid "Idaṃ dutiyaṃ vimuttāyatanaṃ."
msgstr "This is the second opportunity for freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:72.4"
msgid "(9.2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="66"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:73.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno na heva kho satthā dhammaṃ deseti, aññataro "
"vā garuṭṭhāniyo sabrahmacārī, nāpi yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ "
"vitthārena paresaṃ deseti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, it may be that neither the Teacher nor … the mendicant teaches "
"Dharma. But the mendicant recites the Dharma in detail as they learned and "
"memorized it."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn34:73.2"
msgid ""
"Api ca kho yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ vitthārena sajjhāyaṃ karoti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn34:73.3"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, āvuso, bhikkhu yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ vitthārena "
"sajjhāyaṃ karoti tathā tathā so tasmiṃ dhamme atthappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti "
"dhammapaṭisaṃvedī ca."
msgstr ""
"That mendicant feels inspired by the meaning and the teaching in that "
"Dharma, no matter how they recite it in detail as they learned and memorized "
"it."

msgctxt "dn34:73.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa atthappaṭisaṃvedino dhammapaṭisaṃvedino pāmojjaṃ jāyati, pamuditassa "
"pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, "
"sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Feeling inspired, gladness springs up. Being joyful, rapture springs up. "
"When the mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. When the body "
"is tranquil, one feels bliss. And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed."

msgctxt "dn34:73.5"
msgid "Idaṃ tatiyaṃ vimuttāyatanaṃ."
msgstr "This is the third opportunity for freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:73.6"
msgid "(9.3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="67"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:74.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno na heva kho satthā dhammaṃ deseti, aññataro "
"vā garuṭṭhāniyo sabrahmacārī, nāpi yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ "
"vitthārena paresaṃ deseti, nāpi yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ "
"vitthārena sajjhāyaṃ karoti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, it may be that neither the Teacher nor … the mendicant teaches "
"Dharma … nor does the mendicant recite the Dharma. "

msgctxt "dn34:74.2"
msgid ""
"Api ca kho yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ cetasā anuvitakketi "
"anuvicāreti manasānupekkhati."
msgstr ""
"But the mendicant thinks about and considers the Dharma in their heart, "
"examining it with the mind as they learned and memorized it."

msgctxt "dn34:74.3"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, āvuso, bhikkhu yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ cetasā "
"anuvitakketi anuvicāreti manasānupekkhati tathā tathā so tasmiṃ dhamme "
"atthappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti dhammapaṭisaṃvedī ca."
msgstr ""
"That mendicant feels inspired by the meaning and the teaching in that "
"Dharma, no matter how they think about and consider it in their heart, "
"examining it with the mind as they learned and memorized it."

msgctxt "dn34:74.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa atthappaṭisaṃvedino dhammapaṭisaṃvedino pāmojjaṃ jāyati, pamuditassa "
"pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, "
"sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Feeling inspired, gladness springs up. Being joyful, rapture springs up. "
"When the mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. When the body "
"is tranquil, one feels bliss. And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed."

msgctxt "dn34:74.5"
msgid "Idaṃ catutthaṃ vimuttāyatanaṃ."
msgstr "This is the fourth opportunity for freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:74.6"
msgid "(9.4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="68"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:75.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno na heva kho satthā dhammaṃ deseti, aññataro "
"vā garuṭṭhāniyo sabrahmacārī, nāpi yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ "
"vitthārena paresaṃ deseti, nāpi yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ "
"vitthārena sajjhāyaṃ karoti, nāpi yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ cetasā "
"anuvitakketi anuvicāreti manasānupekkhati;"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, it may be that neither the Teacher nor … the mendicant teaches "
"Dharma … nor does the mendicant recite the Dharma … or think about it."

msgctxt "dn34:75.2"
msgid ""
"api ca khvassa aññataraṃ samādhinimittaṃ suggahitaṃ hoti sumanasikataṃ "
"sūpadhāritaṃ suppaṭividdhaṃ paññāya."
msgstr ""
"But a meditation subject as a basis for immersion is properly grasped, "
"attended, borne in mind, and penetrated with wisdom."

msgctxt "dn34:75.3"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, āvuso, bhikkhuno aññataraṃ samādhinimittaṃ suggahitaṃ hoti "
"sumanasikataṃ sūpadhāritaṃ suppaṭividdhaṃ paññāya tathā tathā so tasmiṃ "
"dhamme atthappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti dhammappaṭisaṃvedī ca."
msgstr ""
"That mendicant feels inspired by the meaning and the teaching in that "
"Dharma, no matter how a meditation subject as a basis for immersion is "
"properly grasped, attended, borne in mind, and penetrated with wisdom."

msgctxt "dn34:75.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa atthappaṭisaṃvedino dhammappaṭisaṃvedino pāmojjaṃ jāyati, pamuditassa "
"pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, "
"sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Feeling inspired, gladness springs up. Being joyful, rapture springs up. "
"When the mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. When the body "
"is tranquil, one feels bliss. And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed."

msgctxt "dn34:75.5"
msgid "Idaṃ pañcamaṃ vimuttāyatanaṃ."
msgstr "This is the fifth opportunity for freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:75.6"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā abhiññeyyā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:75.7"
msgid "(9.5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="69"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:76.1"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What five things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:76.2"
msgid "Pañca dhammakkhandhā—"
msgstr "Five spectrums of the teaching:"

msgctxt "dn34:76.3"
msgid ""
"sīlakkhandho, samādhikkhandho, paññākkhandho, vimuttikkhandho, "
"vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandho."
msgstr "ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, knowledge and vision of freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:76.4"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā sacchikātabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(10)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="70"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:77.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ime paññāsa dhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā "
"tathāgatena abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these fifty things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:78.1"
msgid "6. Cha dhammā"
msgstr "Groups of Six"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="71"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.7"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:79.1"
msgid "Cha dhammā bahukārā …"
msgstr "Six things are helpful, etc."

msgctxt "dn34:79.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:79.3"
msgid "cha dhammā sacchikātabbā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="72"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.280"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:80.1"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What six things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:80.2"
msgid "Cha sāraṇīyā dhammā."
msgstr "Six warm-hearted qualities."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn34:80.3"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu āvi "
"ceva raho ca, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo garukaraṇo saṅgahāya "
"avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with "
"bodily kindness, both in public and in private. This warm-hearted quality "
"makes for fondness and respect, conducing to inclusion, harmony, and unity, "
"without fighting. "

msgctxt "dn34:80.4"
msgid "(1.1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="73"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:81.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with "
"verbal kindness."

msgctxt "dn34:81.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:81.3"
msgid "ekībhāvāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:81.4"
msgid "(1.2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="74"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:82.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno mettaṃ manokammaṃ …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with "
"mental kindness."

msgctxt "dn34:82.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:82.3"
msgid "ekībhāvāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:82.4"
msgid "(1.3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="75"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:83.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu ye te lābhā dhammikā dhammaladdhā antamaso "
"pattapariyāpannamattampi, tathārūpehi lābhehi appaṭivibhattabhogī hoti "
"sīlavantehi sabrahmacārīhi sādhāraṇabhogī, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant shares without reservation any material possessions "
"they have gained by legitimate means, even the food placed in the alms-bowl, "
"using them in common with their ethical spiritual companions. "

msgctxt "dn34:83.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:83.3"
msgid "ekībhāvāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:83.4"
msgid "(1.4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="76"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:84.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu, yāni tāni sīlāni akhaṇḍāni acchiddāni "
"asabalāni akammāsāni bhujissāni viññuppasatthāni aparāmaṭṭhāni "
"samādhisaṃvattanikāni, tathārūpesu sīlesu sīlasāmaññagato viharati "
"sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant lives according to the precepts shared with their "
"spiritual companions, both in public and in private. Those precepts are "
"uncorrupted, unflawed, unblemished, untainted, liberating, praised by "
"sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to samādhi. "

msgctxt "dn34:84.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:84.3"
msgid "ekībhāvāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:84.4"
msgid "(1.5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="77"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:85.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu yāyaṃ diṭṭhi ariyā niyyānikā niyyāti takkarassa "
"sammā dukkhakkhayāya, tathārūpāya diṭṭhiyā diṭṭhi sāmaññagato viharati "
"sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo "
"garukaraṇo, saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā ekībhāvāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant lives according to the view shared with their "
"spiritual companions, both in public and in private. That view is noble and "
"emancipating, and leads one who practices it to the complete end of "
"suffering. This warm-hearted quality makes for fondness and respect, "
"conducing to inclusion, harmony, and unity, without fighting. "

msgctxt "dn34:85.2"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā bahukārā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:85.3"
msgid "(1.6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="78"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:86.1"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What six things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:86.2"
msgid "Cha anussatiṭṭhānāni—"
msgstr "Six recollections:"

msgctxt "dn34:86.3"
msgid ""
"buddhānussati, dhammānussati, saṅghānussati, sīlānussati, cāgānussati, "
"devatānussati."
msgstr ""
"the recollection of the Buddha, the teaching, the Saṅgha, ethics, "
"generosity, and the gods."

msgctxt "dn34:86.4"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā bhāvetabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="79"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:87.1"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What six things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:87.2"
msgid "Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni—"
msgstr "Six interior sense fields:"

msgctxt "dn34:87.3"
msgid ""
"cakkhāyatanaṃ, sotāyatanaṃ, ghānāyatanaṃ, jivhāyatanaṃ, kāyāyatanaṃ, "
"manāyatanaṃ."
msgstr "eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind."

msgctxt "dn34:87.4"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā pariññeyyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="80"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:88.1"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What six things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:88.2"
msgid "Cha taṇhākāyā—"
msgstr "Six classes of craving:"

msgctxt "dn34:88.3"
msgid ""
"rūpataṇhā, saddataṇhā, gandhataṇhā, rasataṇhā, phoṭṭhabbataṇhā, dhammataṇhā."
msgstr "craving for sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts."

msgctxt "dn34:88.4"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā pahātabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="81"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:89.1"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What six things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:89.2"
msgid "Cha agāravā—"
msgstr "Six kinds of disrespect."

msgctxt "dn34:89.3"
msgid "idhāvuso, bhikkhu satthari agāravo viharati appatisso."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant lacks respect and reverence for the Teacher, the teaching, and "
"the Saṅgha, the training, diligence, and hospitality."

msgctxt "dn34:89.4"
