#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="191"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:203.1"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What nine things are hard to penetrate?"

msgctxt "dn34:203.2"
msgid "Nava nānattā—"
msgstr "Nine kinds of diversity."

#. VAR: () → (lābhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati ­mañña­nā­nānat­taṃ) (bj)
msgctxt "dn34:203.3"
msgid ""
"dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, phassanānattaṃ paṭicca "
"uppajjati vedanānānattaṃ, vedanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, "
"saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṅkappanānattaṃ, saṅkappanānattaṃ paṭicca "
"uppajjati chandanānattaṃ, chandanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariḷāhanānattaṃ, "
"pariḷāhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariyesanānānattaṃ, pariyesanānānattaṃ "
"paṭicca uppajjati lābhanānattaṃ ()."
msgstr ""
"Diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts. Diversity of "
"contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings. Diversity of feelings gives "
"rise to diversity of perceptions. Diversity of perceptions gives rise to "
"diversity of intentions. Diversity of intentions gives rise to diversity of "
"desires. Diversity of desires gives rise to diversity of passions. Diversity "
"of passions gives rise to diversity of searches. Diversity of searches gives "
"rise to diversity of gains."

msgctxt "dn34:203.4"
msgid "Ime nava dhammā duppaṭivijjhā. <span class=\"brnum\">(7)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="192"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.290"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:204.1"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What nine things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:204.2"
msgid "Nava saññā—"
msgstr "Nine perceptions:"

msgctxt "dn34:204.3"
msgid ""
"asubhasaññā, maraṇasaññā, āhārepaṭikūlasaññā, sabbalokeanabhiratisaññā, "
"aniccasaññā, anicce dukkhasaññā, dukkhe anattasaññā, pahānasaññā, "
"virāgasaññā."
msgstr ""
"The perceptions of ugliness, death, repulsiveness in food, dissatisfaction "
"with the whole world, impermanence, suffering in impermanence, and not-self "
"in suffering, giving up, and fading away. "

msgctxt "dn34:204.4"
msgid "Ime nava dhammā uppādetabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(8)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="193"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:205.1"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What nine things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:205.2"
msgid "Nava anupubbavihārā—"
msgstr "Nine progressive meditations."

msgctxt "dn34:205.3"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ "
"savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unwholesome qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption …"

msgctxt "dn34:205.4"
msgid "Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:205.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:205.6"
msgid "dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "second absorption …"

msgctxt "dn34:205.7"
msgid "Pītiyā ca virāgā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:205.8"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:205.9"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "dn34:205.10"
msgid "Sukhassa ca pahānā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:205.11"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:205.12"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

msgctxt "dn34:205.13"
msgid "Sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā …"
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of "
"impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is "
"infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn34:205.14"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn34:205.15"
msgid "ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:205.16"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti "
"viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space—aware that ‘"
"consciousness is infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of "
"infinite consciousness."

msgctxt "dn34:205.17"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘"
"there is nothing at all’, they enter and remain in the dimension of "
"nothingness."

msgctxt "dn34:205.18"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, they enter and remain in "
"the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception."

msgctxt "dn34:205.19"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, "
"they enter and remain in the cessation of perception and feeling."

msgctxt "dn34:205.20"
msgid "Ime nava dhammā abhiññeyyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(9)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="194"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:206.1"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What nine things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:206.2"
msgid "Nava anupubbanirodhā—"
msgstr "Nine progressive cessations. "

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn34:206.3"
msgid ""
"paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa kāmasaññā niruddhā hoti, dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ "
"samāpannassa vitakkavicārā niruddhā honti, tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa pīti "
"niruddhā hoti, catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa assāsapassāssā niruddhā honti, "
"ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samāpannassa rūpasaññā niruddhā hoti, viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ "
"samāpannassa ākāsānañcāyatanasaññā niruddhā hoti, ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ "
"samāpannassa viññāṇañcāyatanasaññā niruddhā hoti, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ "
"samāpannassa ākiñcaññāyatanasaññā niruddhā hoti, saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"samāpannassa saññā ca vedanā ca niruddhā honti."
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the first absorption, sensual perceptions have "
"ceased. For someone who has attained the second absorption, the placing of "
"the mind and keeping it connected have ceased. For someone who has attained "
"the third absorption, rapture has ceased. For someone who has attained the "
"fourth absorption, breathing has ceased. For someone who has attained the "
"dimension of infinite space, the perception of form has ceased. For someone "
"who has attained the dimension of infinite consciousness, the perception of "
"the dimension of infinite space has ceased. For someone who has attained the "
"dimension of nothingness, the perception of the dimension of infinite "
"consciousness has ceased. For someone who has attained the dimension of "
"neither perception nor non-perception, the perception of the dimension of "
"nothingness has ceased. For someone who has attained the cessation of "
"perception and feeling, perception and feeling have ceased."

msgctxt "dn34:206.4"
msgid "Ime nava dhammā sacchikātabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(10)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="195"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:207.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ime navuti dhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā "
"tathāgatena abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these ninety things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:208.1"
msgid "10. Dasa dhammā"
msgstr "Groups of Ten"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="196"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.3"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:209.1"
msgid "Dasa dhammā bahukārā …"
msgstr ""
"Ten things are helpful, ten things should be developed, ten things should be "
"completely understood, ten things should be given up, ten things make things "
"worse, ten things lead to distinction, ten things are hard to penetrate, ten "
"things should be produced, ten things should be directly known, ten things "
"should be realized."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn34:209.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn34:209.3"
msgid "dasa dhammā sacchikātabbā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="197"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:210.1"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What ten things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:210.2"
msgid "Dasa nāthakaraṇā dhammā—"
msgstr "Ten qualities that serve as protector."

msgctxt "dn34:210.3"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati "
"ācāragocarasampanno, aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī samādāya sikkhati "
"sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, and has "
"appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest flaw, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken. "

msgctxt "dn34:210.4"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:210.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:210.6"
msgid "sikkhati sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:210.7"
msgid "Ayampi dhammo nāthakaraṇo."
msgstr "This is a quality that serves as protector."

msgctxt "dn34:210.8"
