#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="205"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:218.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu satimā hoti, paramena satinepakkena "
"samannāgato, cirakatampi cirabhāsitampi saritā anussaritā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is mindful. They have utmost mindfulness and "
"alertness, and can remember and recall what was said and done long ago."

msgctxt "dn34:218.2"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:218.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:218.4"
msgid "ayampi dhammo nāthakaraṇo."
msgstr "This too is a quality that serves as protector."

msgctxt "dn34:218.5"
msgid "(1.9)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="206"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:219.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya "
"samannāgato, ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is wise. They have the wisdom of arising and "
"passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending "
"of suffering."

msgctxt "dn34:219.2"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:219.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:219.4"
msgid "ayampi dhammo nāthakaraṇo."
msgstr "This too is a quality that serves as protector."

msgctxt "dn34:219.5"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā bahukārā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:219.6"
msgid "(1.10)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="207"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:220.1"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What ten things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:220.2"
msgid "Dasa kasiṇāyatanāni—"
msgstr "Ten universal dimensions of meditation."

msgctxt "dn34:220.3"
msgid "pathavīkasiṇameko sañjānāti uddhaṃ adho tiriyaṃ advayaṃ appamāṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Someone perceives the meditation on universal earth above, below, across, "
"non-dual and limitless. "

msgctxt "dn34:220.4"
msgid "Āpokasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "They perceive the meditation on universal water … "

msgctxt "dn34:220.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:220.6"
msgid "tejokasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal fire … "

msgctxt "dn34:220.7"
msgid "vāyokasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal air … "

msgctxt "dn34:220.8"
msgid "nīlakasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal blue … "

msgctxt "dn34:220.9"
msgid "pītakasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal yellow … "

msgctxt "dn34:220.10"
msgid "lohitakasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal red … "

msgctxt "dn34:220.11"
msgid "odātakasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal white …"

msgctxt "dn34:220.12"
msgid "ākāsakasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal space … "

msgctxt "dn34:220.13"
msgid "viññāṇakasiṇameko sañjānāti uddhaṃ adho tiriyaṃ advayaṃ appamāṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They perceive the meditation on universal consciousness above, below, "
"across, non-dual and limitless. "

msgctxt "dn34:220.14"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā bhāvetabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="208"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:221.1"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What ten things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:221.2"
msgid "Dasāyatanāni—"
msgstr "Ten sense fields:"

msgctxt "dn34:221.3"
msgid ""
"cakkhāyatanaṃ, rūpāyatanaṃ, sotāyatanaṃ, saddāyatanaṃ, ghānāyatanaṃ, "
"gandhāyatanaṃ, jivhāyatanaṃ, rasāyatanaṃ, kāyāyatanaṃ, phoṭṭhabbāyatanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"eye and forms, ear and sounds, nose and smells, tongue and tastes, body and "
"touches."

msgctxt "dn34:221.4"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā pariññeyyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="209"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:222.1"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What ten things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:222.2"
msgid "Dasa micchattā—"
msgstr "Ten wrong ways:"

msgctxt "dn34:222.3"
msgid ""
"micchādiṭṭhi, micchāsaṅkappo, micchāvācā, micchākammanto, micchāājīvo, "
"micchāvāyāmo, micchāsati, micchāsamādhi, micchāñāṇaṃ, micchāvimutti."
msgstr ""
"wrong view, wrong motivation, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, "
"wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:222.4"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā pahātabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="210"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:223.1"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What ten things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:223.2"
msgid "Dasa akusalakammapathā—"
msgstr "Ten ways of doing unwholesome deeds:"

msgctxt "dn34:223.3"
msgid ""
"pāṇātipāto, adinnādānaṃ, kāmesumicchācāro, musāvādo, pisuṇā vācā, pharusā "
"vācā, samphappalāpo, abhijjhā, byāpādo, micchādiṭṭhi."
msgstr ""
"killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; speech that’s "
"lying, divisive, harsh, or meaningless; covetousness, ill will, and wrong "
"view. "

msgctxt "dn34:223.4"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā hānabhāgiyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="211"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.291"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:224.1"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What eight things lead to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:224.2"
msgid "Dasa kusalakammapathā—"
msgstr "Ten ways of doing wholesome deeds:"

msgctxt "dn34:224.3"
msgid ""
"pāṇātipātā veramaṇī, adinnādānā veramaṇī, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī, "
"musāvādā veramaṇī, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī, "
"samphappalāpā veramaṇī, anabhijjhā, abyāpādo, sammādiṭṭhi."
msgstr ""
"refraining from killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; "
"avoiding speech that’s lying, divisive, harsh, or meaningless; contentment, "
"good will, and right view. "

msgctxt "dn34:224.4"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā visesabhāgiyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="212"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:225.1"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What ten things are hard to penetrate?"

msgctxt "dn34:225.2"
msgid "Dasa ariyavāsā—"
msgstr "Ten noble abodes."

msgctxt "dn34:225.3"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu pañcaṅgavippahīno hoti, chaḷaṅgasamannāgato, ekārakkho, "
"caturāpasseno, paṇunnapaccekasacco, samavayasaṭṭhesano, anāvilasaṅkappo, "
"passaddhakāyasaṅkhāro, suvimuttacitto, suvimuttapañño."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant has given up five factors, possesses six factors, has a single "
"guard, has four supports, has eliminated idiosyncratic interpretations of "
"the truth, has totally given up searching, has unsullied motivations, has "
"stilled the physical process, and is well freed in mind and well freed by "
"wisdom. "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="213"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:226.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu pañcaṅgavippahīno hoti?"
msgstr "And how has a mendicant given up five qualities? "

msgctxt "dn34:226.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno kāmacchando pahīno hoti, byāpādo pahīno hoti, "
"thinamiddhaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, vicikicchā pahīnā "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant has given up sensual desire, ill will, dullness and "
"drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, and doubt.  "

msgctxt "dn34:226.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu pañcaṅgavippahīno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has given up five qualities."

msgctxt "dn34:226.4"
msgid "(7.1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="214"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:227.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu chaḷaṅgasamannāgato hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant possess six factors?"

msgctxt "dn34:227.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā neva sumano hoti na dummano, "
"upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant, seeing a sight with their eyes, is neither happy nor sad. They "
"remain equanimous, mindful and aware. "

msgctxt "dn34:227.3"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …"
msgstr "Hearing a sound with the ears …"

msgctxt "dn34:227.4"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:227.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "Smelling an odor with the nose …"

msgctxt "dn34:227.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "Tasting a flavor with the tongue …"

msgctxt "dn34:227.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "Feeling a touch with the body …"

msgctxt "dn34:227.8"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya neva sumano hoti na dummano, upekkhako viharati sato "
"sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"Knowing a thought with their mind, they’re neither happy nor sad. They "
"remain equanimous, mindful and aware."

msgctxt "dn34:227.9"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu chaḷaṅgasamannāgato hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant possess six factors."

msgctxt "dn34:227.10"
msgid "(7.2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="215"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:228.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu ekārakkho hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant have a single guard?"

msgctxt "dn34:228.2"
msgid "Idhāvuso, bhikkhu satārakkhena cetasā samannāgato hoti."
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant’s heart is guarded by mindfulness."

msgctxt "dn34:228.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu ekārakkho hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has a single guard."

msgctxt "dn34:228.4"
msgid "(7.3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="216"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:229.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu caturāpasseno hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant have four supports?"

msgctxt "dn34:229.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu saṅkhāyekaṃ paṭisevati, saṅkhāyekaṃ adhivāseti, "
"saṅkhāyekaṃ parivajjeti, saṅkhāyekaṃ vinodeti."
msgstr ""
"After reflection, a mendicant uses some things, endures some things, avoids "
"some things, and gets rid of some things."

msgctxt "dn34:229.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu caturāpasseno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has four supports."

msgctxt "dn34:229.4"
msgid "(7.4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="217"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:230.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu paṇunnapaccekasacco hoti?"
msgstr ""
"And how has a mendicant eliminated idiosyncratic interpretations of the "
"truth?"

msgctxt "dn34:230.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno yāni tāni puthusamaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ puthupaccekasaccāni, "
"sabbāni tāni nunnāni honti paṇunnāni cattāni vantāni muttāni pahīnāni "
"paṭinissaṭṭhāni."
msgstr ""
"Different ascetics and brahmins have different idiosyncratic interpretations "
"of the truth. A mendicant has dispelled, eliminated, thrown out, rejected, "
"let go of, given up, and relinquished all these."

msgctxt "dn34:230.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu paṇunnapaccekasacco hoti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant has eliminated idiosyncratic interpretations of the "
"truth."

msgctxt "dn34:230.4"
msgid "(7.5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="218"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:231.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu samavayasaṭṭhesano hoti?"
msgstr "And how has a mendicant totally given up searching?"

msgctxt "dn34:231.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno kāmesanā pahīnā hoti, bhavesanā pahīnā hoti, "
"brahmacariyesanā paṭippassaddhā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when they’ve given up searching for sensual pleasures, for continued "
"existence, and for a spiritual path. "

msgctxt "dn34:231.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu samavayasaṭṭhesano hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has totally given up searching."

msgctxt "dn34:231.4"
msgid "(7.6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="219"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:232.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu anāvilasaṅkappā hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant have unsullied intentions?"

msgctxt "dn34:232.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno kāmasaṅkappo pahīno hoti, byāpādasaṅkappo pahīno hoti, "
"vihiṃsāsaṅkappo pahīno hoti."
msgstr "It’s when they’ve given up sensual, malicious, and cruel intentions."

msgctxt "dn34:232.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu anāvilasaṅkappo hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has unsullied intentions."

msgctxt "dn34:232.4"
msgid "(7.7)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="220"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:233.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu passaddhakāyasaṅkhāro hoti?"
msgstr "And how has a mendicant stilled the physical process?"

msgctxt "dn34:233.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva "
"somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they "
"enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with "
"pure equanimity and mindfulness. "

msgctxt "dn34:233.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu passaddhakāyasaṅkhāro hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has stilled the physical process."

msgctxt "dn34:233.4"
msgid "(7.8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="221"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:234.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu suvimuttacitto hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant well freed in mind?"

msgctxt "dn34:234.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno rāgā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ hoti, dosā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ hoti, "
"mohā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ hoti."
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant’s mind is freed from greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "dn34:234.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu suvimuttacitto hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is well freed in mind."

msgctxt "dn34:234.4"
msgid "(7.9)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="222"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:235.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu suvimuttapañño hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant well freed by wisdom?"

msgctxt "dn34:235.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu ‘rāgo me pahīno ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato "
"āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant understands: ‘I’ve given up greed, hate, and delusion, "
"cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, exterminated them, so "
"they’re unable to arise in the future.’"

msgctxt "dn34:235.3"
msgid "‘Doso me pahīno …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:235.4"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:235.5"
msgid "āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:235.6"
msgid "‘Moho me pahīno …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:235.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:235.8"
msgid "āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:235.9"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu suvimuttapañño hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant’s mind is well freed by wisdom."

msgctxt "dn34:235.10"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā duppaṭivijjhā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:235.11"
msgid "(7.10)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="223"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:236.1"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What ten things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:236.2"
msgid "Dasa saññā—"
msgstr "Ten perceptions."

msgctxt "dn34:236.3"
msgid ""
"asubhasaññā, maraṇasaññā, āhārepaṭikūlasaññā, sabbalokeanabhiratisaññā, "
"aniccasaññā, anicce dukkhasaññā, dukkhe anattasaññā, pahānasaññā, "
"virāgasaññā, nirodhasaññā."
msgstr ""
"The perceptions of ugliness, death, repulsiveness in food, dissatisfaction "
"with the whole world, impermanence, suffering in impermanence, and not-self "
"in suffering, giving up, fading away, and cessation. "

msgctxt "dn34:236.4"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā uppādetabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(8)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="224"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:237.1"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What ten things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:237.2"
msgid "Dasa nijjaravatthūni—"
msgstr "Ten grounds for wearing away."

msgctxt "dn34:237.3"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhissa micchādiṭṭhi nijjiṇṇā hoti."
msgstr "For one of right view, wrong view is worn away."

msgctxt "dn34:237.4"
msgid ""
"Ye ca micchādiṭṭhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, te cassa "
"nijjiṇṇā honti."
msgstr ""
"And the many bad, unwholesome qualities that arise because of wrong view are "
"worn away."

msgctxt "dn34:237.5"
msgid "Sammāsaṅkappassa micchāsaṅkappo …"
msgstr "For one of right intention, wrong intention is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:237.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:237.7"
msgid "sammāvācassa micchāvācā …"
msgstr "For one of right speech, wrong speech is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:237.8"
msgid "sammākammantassa micchākammanto …"
msgstr "For one of right action, wrong action is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:237.9"
msgid "sammāājīvassa micchāājīvo …"
msgstr "For one of right livelihood, wrong livelihood is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:237.10"
msgid "sammāvāyāmassa micchāvāyāmo …"
msgstr "For one of right effort, wrong effort is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:237.11"
msgid "sammāsatissa micchāsati …"
msgstr "For one of right mindfulness, wrong mindfulness is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:237.12"
msgid "sammāsamādhissa micchāsamādhi …"
msgstr "For one of right immersion, wrong immersion is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:237.13"
msgid "sammāñāṇassa micchāñāṇaṃ nijjiṇṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr "For one of right knowledge, wrong knowledge is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:237.14"
msgid "Sammāvimuttissa micchāvimutti nijjiṇṇā hoti."
msgstr "For one of right freedom, wrong freedom is worn away."

msgctxt "dn34:237.15"
msgid ""
"Ye ca micchāvimuttipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, te cassa "
"nijjiṇṇā honti."
msgstr ""
"And the many bad, unwholesome qualities that arise because of wrong freedom "
"are worn away."

msgctxt "dn34:237.16"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā abhiññeyyā. <span class=\"brnum\">(9)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="225"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.292"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:238.1"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What ten things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:238.2"
msgid "Dasa asekkhā dhammā—"
msgstr "Ten qualities of an adept."

msgctxt "dn34:238.3"
msgid ""
"asekkhā sammādiṭṭhi, asekkho sammāsaṅkappo, asekkhā sammāvācā, asekkho "
"sammākammanto, asekkho sammāājīvo, asekkho sammāvāyāmo, asekkhā sammāsati, "
"asekkho sammāsamādhi, asekkhaṃ sammāñāṇaṃ, asekkhā sammāvimutti."
msgstr ""
"An adept’s right view, right motivation, right speech, right action, right "
"livelihood, right mindfulness, right samādhi, right knowledge, and right "
"freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:238.4"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā sacchikātabbā. <span class=\"brnum\">(10)</span>"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="226"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:239.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ime satadhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā tathāgatena "
"abhisambuddhā”ti."
msgstr ""
"So these hundred things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

msgctxt "dn34:239.2"
msgid "Idamavocāyasmā sāriputto."
msgstr "This is what Venerable Sāriputta said."

msgctxt "dn34:239.3"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Uplifted, the mendicants approved of what Sāriputta said."

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn34:240.1"
msgid "Dasuttarasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ ekādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn34:241.1"
msgid "Pāthikavaggo niṭṭhito."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p><a class="sc" id="227"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts3.293"></a>
#. VAR: Pāthiko ca udumbaraṃ → pāṭikañca udumbaraṃ (s1-3, km) |
#. pāṭi­kodum­barī­ceva (pts1)
msgctxt "dn34:242.1"
msgid "Pāthiko ca udumbaraṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:242.2"
msgid "cakkavatti aggaññakaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:242.3"
msgid "Sampasādanapāsādaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:242.4"
msgid "mahāpurisalakkhaṇaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="228"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:243.1"
msgid "Siṅgālāṭānāṭiyakaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:243.2"
msgid "saṅgīti ca dasuttaraṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:243.3"
msgid "Ekādasahi suttehi,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:243.4"
msgid "pāthikavaggoti vuccati."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endbook">
msgctxt "dn34:244.1"
msgid "Pāthikavaggapāḷi niṭṭhitā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn34:245.1"
msgid "Tīhi vaggehi paṭimaṇḍito sakalo"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endbook">
msgctxt "dn34:246.1"
msgid "dīghanikāyo samatto."
msgstr "The Long Discourses is completed."
